This paper deals with analyzing the security of mobile urban communication networks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper specifically focuses on the effect of colluding attackers on the message delivery rate, which is a security concern (cs.CR). The paper also proposes an evolutionary algorithm to solve the optimization problem, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper uses simulations to model the network scenarios, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper deals with a novel form of the Social Internet of Things, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
